{
  "page": "Denys Marbrand",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> Denys Marbrand's canon status is currently unclear. He is not mentioned in the published works of <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>. However, he is mentioned in the <a href=\"/index.php/The_Hedge_Knight_(comics)\" title=\"The Hedge Knight (comics)\">graphic novel adaptation</a> of <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Hedge_Knight\" title=\"The Hedge Knight\">The Hedge Knight</a></i>, in the <a href=\"/index.php/List_of_characters_and_arms_in_The_Hedge_Knight_graphic_novel_collection\" title=\"List of characters and arms in The Hedge Knight graphic novel collection\">roll of arms</a> of the attendees of the <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_at_Ashford_Meadow\" title=\"Tourney at Ashford Meadow\">tourney at Ashford Meadow</a>. He is further mentioned in an expanded version of the Westerlands chapter from <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The World of Ice and Fire\">The World of Ice and Fire</a></i> that was published on Martin's website a few months before the book release date.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Until further information comes out, he should be considered a semi-canon character.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Marbrand\" title=\"House Marbrand\"><img alt=\"House Marbrand.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d4/House_Marbrand.svg/50px-House_Marbrand.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d4/House_Marbrand.svg/75px-House_Marbrand.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d4/House_Marbrand.svg/100px-House_Marbrand.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Ser</span><br />Denys Marbrand</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Marbrand\" title=\"House Marbrand\"><img alt=\"House Marbrand.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d4/House_Marbrand.svg/50px-House_Marbrand.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d4/House_Marbrand.svg/75px-House_Marbrand.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d4/House_Marbrand.svg/100px-House_Marbrand.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Marbrand\" title=\"House Marbrand\">House Marbrand</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">Westermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nin or before <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_194_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">194&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_255_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">255&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">Westerlands</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Hedge_Knight\" title=\"The Hedge Knight\">The Hedge Knight</a></i> (roll of arms)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Denys Marbrand</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Marbrand\" title=\"House Marbrand\">House Marbrand</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron II Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.5B.5Bthe_hedge_knight_.28comics.29.7Cgraphic_novel.5D.5D.2C_2nd_edition.2C_.5B.5Blist_of_characters_and_arms_in_the_hedge_knight_graphic_novel_collection.7Croll_of_arms.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.5B.5Bthe_hedge_knight_.28comics.29.7Cgraphic_novel.5D.5D.2C_2nd_edition.2C_.5B.5Blist_of_characters_and_arms_in_the_hedge_knight_graphic_novel_collection.7Croll_of_arms.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> He may have lived through the reigns of kings <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys I Targaryen\">Aerys I</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Maekar_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maekar I Targaryen\">Maekar I</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon V Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Behind_the_Scenes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Behind the Scenes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Denys_Marbrand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/209_AC\" title=\"209 AC\">209&#160;AC</a>, during the reign of <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Daeron II Targaryen\">Daeron II Targaryen</a>, a participant in the <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_at_Ashford_Meadow\" title=\"Tourney at Ashford Meadow\">tourney at Ashford Meadow</a> fought under the Marbrand banner.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Although it is semi-canon information, in the comic book adaptation of <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Hedge_Knight\" title=\"The Hedge Knight\">The Hedge Knight</a></i> the name of Ser Denys Marbrand is given on the roll of arms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.5B.5Bthe_hedge_knight_.28comics.29.7Cgraphic_novel.5D.5D.2C_2nd_edition.2C_.5B.5Blist_of_characters_and_arms_in_the_hedge_knight_graphic_novel_collection.7Croll_of_arms.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.5B.5Bthe_hedge_knight_.28comics.29.7Cgraphic_novel.5D.5D.2C_2nd_edition.2C_.5B.5Blist_of_characters_and_arms_in_the_hedge_knight_graphic_novel_collection.7Croll_of_arms.5D.5D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Behind_the_Scenes\">Behind the Scenes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Denys_Marbrand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Behind the Scenes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>According to the unabridged version of \"The Westerlands\" chapter from <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Lord Denys Marbrand was the father of Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Marbrand\" title=\"Jeyne Marbrand\">Jeyne Marbrand</a>, wife to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos Lannister</a>. In this earlier draft of the chapter, when Tytos became Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>, Denys was his chief supporter, a \"pillar of strength\" for his daughter and her husband. In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_255_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">255&#160;AC</a>, when King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon V Targaryen</a> became angered with the over-grasping <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarbeck\" title=\"House Tarbeck\">House Tarbeck</a>, Tytos sent Denys (still grieving the recent death of his daughter Jeyne) to capture Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walderan_Tarbeck\" title=\"Walderan Tarbeck\">Walderan Tarbeck</a> and Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Reyne\" title=\"Ellyn Reyne\">Ellyn Tarbeck</a>, to bring them to Casterly Rock to answer for their crimes. However, <a href=\"/index.php/Roger_Reyne\" title=\"Roger Reyne\">Roger Reyne</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Castamere\" title=\"Lord of Castamere\">Lord of Castamere</a> and Ellyn's brother, led a host in attacking the Marbrand men in the night before they reached <a href=\"/index.php/Tarbeck_Hall\" title=\"Tarbeck Hall\">Tarbeck Hall</a>, slaying hundreds, including the old warrior Denys. Though Tytos became extremely angry, and calls went out for war, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Reynard_Reyne\" title=\"Reynard Reyne\">Reynard Reyne</a> convinced Tytos that the attack was a \"tragic misunderstanding\", claiming that Roger was unaware of Denys's identity and thought he was attacking a band of <a href=\"/index.php/Outlaw\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Outlaw\">outlaws</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Robber_knight\" title=\"Robber knight\">robber knights</a>. Once Reynard offered apologies and a <a href=\"/index.php/Blood_price\" title=\"Blood price\">blood price</a> to House Marbrand, Tytos pardoned Roger Reyne, and Lord and Lady Tarbeck as well.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the published version of the chapter, however, Jeyne's father was changed to <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Marbrand\" title=\"Alyn Marbrand\">Alyn Marbrand</a>, and no such incident with the Reynes and Tarbecks is mentioned.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands:_house_lannister_under_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Denys and Alyn have \"some relation\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Denys_Marbrand&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Marbrand\" title=\"Alyn Marbrand\">Alyn</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Unknown<br />wife</td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Denys</a></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td></tr><tr align=\"center\"><td style=\"border-right:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><sp